Package apache.conf.parser

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ConfigurationLine
    This class is used to model a configuration line from the Apache Configuration

    A configuration line consists of the following:
    line - The unmodified line(s) from the Apache Configuration.
    Directive
    Class used to model an Apache directive.
    DirectiveParser
    This class is used to parse the Apache configuration and obtain directives.
    Enclosure
    Class used to model an Apache enclosure.
    EnclosureParser
    This class is used to parse the Apache configuration and obtain enclosures.
    File
    This class provides an extension of the built in java.io.File class.
    ParsableLine
    Class used to give information on whether a line in the configuration is parsable.
    If a line is parsable then the include value will be set to true.
    Parser
    This class is used to provide generic parser functionality for the Apache configuration.
